org.knime.base.data.aggregation.dialogutil

Class AbstractAggregationPanel<T extends AggregationTableModel<R>,R extends AggregationFunctionRow<?>,L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.event.MouseAdapter
      • org.knime.base.data.aggregation.dialogutil.AbstractAggregationPanel<T,R,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the AggregationTableModel implementation to work with
    R - the AggregationFunctionRow implementation to work with
    L - the class of the list elements the user can choose from
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MouseListener, MouseMotionListener, MouseWheelListener, EventListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AggregationColumnPanel, AggregationColumnPanel, ColumnAggregationPanel, DataTypeAggregationPanel, DBColumnAggregationFunctionPanel, DBDataTypeAggregationFunctionPanel, DBPatternAggregationFunctionPanel, PatternAggregationPanel

    public abstract class AbstractAggregationPanel<T extends AggregationTableModel<R>,R extends AggregationFunctionRow<?>,L>
extends MouseAdapter
    Abstract class that creates a panel which contains a list of Objects defined by the parameter O to select from on the left side of the panel, a box with add an remove buttons in the middle and a table of type AggregationTableModel that contains the selected options from the left with additional information on the right.
    Author:
    Tobias Koetter, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland
    See Also:
    AggregationTableModel, AggregationFunctionRow
